According to the [http://www.ditzionariu.org Sardinian dictionary] '''pibinca''' means [[nuisance]].
Recently, the word has gained a new meaning when preceded by the artcile "sa" (the femenine article [[the]] in the [[Sardinian language]]), to indicate the ex-[[Cagliari Calcio]] footballer [[Dario Silva]], who used to frenzily but ineffectively struggle against the opponent defending lines.

